# JavaScript Functionality Guidelines

The site uses jQuery and vanilla JavaScript for interactive features.

## Core Functionality in [js/index.js](mdc:js/index.js)

### Publication Mouseover Effects
- `.publication-mousecell` elements support image/video transitions
- On mouseover: Hide `img`, show `video` and `.image2` elements
- On mouseout: Show `img`, hide `video` and `.image2` elements
- Touch support: `touchstart`/`touchmove` triggers show, `touchend` triggers hide

### Navigation Features
- **Burger menu**: Toggles `.is-active` class on navbar burger and menu
- **Auto-close**: Clicking navbar items automatically closes mobile menu
- **External links**: All links (except anchors) automatically open in new tabs

### Event Handling
- Uses `$(document).ready()` for jQuery initialization
- Uses `document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded')` for vanilla JS
- Proper event delegation for dynamic content

## Dependencies
- **jQuery 3.6.0**: Loaded from Google CDN
- **Font Awesome 6.5.2**: For icons
- **Academicons**: For academic-specific icons
- **Google Fonts**: Google Sans and Noto Sans

## Best Practices
- Maintain separation between jQuery and vanilla JS code
- Use proper event cleanup to prevent memory leaks
- Ensure touch device compatibility for all interactive elements
- Keep external link behavior consistent
- Test mobile navigation thoroughly

## Interactive Elements
- Navbar burger menu toggle
- Publication image/video hover effects
- External link handling
- Touch-friendly mobile interactions

When modifying JavaScript, ensure compatibility with both desktop and mobile browsers, and maintain the existing jQuery/vanilla JS patterns.
